businessRule.name: OP_MLE_SolutionHelper
businessRule.sourceCode:
Imports System Imports System.Data Imports System.Data.Common Imports System.IO Imports System.Collections.Generic Imports System.Globalization Imports System.Linq Imports Microsoft.VisualBasic Imports System.Windows.Forms Imports OneStream.Shared.Common Imports OneStream.Shared.Wcf Imports OneStream.Shared.Engine Imports OneStream.Shared.Database Imports OneStream.Stage.Engine Imports OneStream.Stage.Database Imports OneStream.Finance.Engine Imports OneStream.Finance.Database Imports System.Deployment.Internal Imports System.Security.Cryptography Imports System.Text Imports System.Text.RegularExpressions
Imports System.Xml.Linq
Namespace OneStream.BusinessRule.DashboardExtender.OP_MLE_SolutionHelper Public Class MainClass
Public Function Main(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal globals As BRGlobals, ByVal api As Object, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As Object Try
Select Case args.FunctionType Case Is = DashboardExtenderFunctionType.LoadDashboard If args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("OnLoad") Then If args.LoadDashboardTaskInfo.Reason = LoadDashboardReasonType.Initialize And args.LoadDashboardTaskInfo.Action = LoadDashboardActionType.BeforeFirstGetParameters Then 'Initialize Viewer to appropriate dashboard Dim loadDashboardTaskResult As New XFLoadDashboardTaskResult() loadDashboardTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("SelectPage_OP_MLE", "3_Content_OP_MLEM") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("SelectedPage_OP_MLE", "Home") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_MLEH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutCreatedBy_OP_MLEH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpABoutVersion_OP_MLEH", "") loadDashboardTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars.Add("HelpAboutSolutionTitle_OP_MLEH", "") Return loadDashboardTaskResult End If End If Case Is = DashboardExtenderFunctionType.ComponentSelectionChanged
If (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Uninstall")) Then 'Standard Setup: Uninstall UI Interface and Solution Data Tables Return Me.UninstallSolution(si, args)
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("CreateSolutionTables")) Then Return CreateSolutionTables(si, args)
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("DashboardNav")) Then Dim dashboardName As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("content", String.Empty) BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectPage_OP_MLE", dashboardName) If dashboardName.Equals("3_Content_OP_MLEM") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_MLE", "Home") ElseIf dashboardName.Equals("0_Settings_OP_MLES") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_MLE", "Settings") ElseIf dashboardName.Equals("0_Help_OP_MLEH") Then BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "SelectedPage_OP_MLE", "Help") End If
ElseIf (args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ValidateSetupStepsExecuted")) Then Return ValidateSetupStepsExecuted(si, args)
#Region "OP_MLE Custom Rules"
#Region "Get Metadata Dimensions"
ElseIf args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("GetMetadataDimensions") Then
Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
Dim metadataFilePath As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pImportFileLocation_OP_MLE") Dim xml As String = Me.GetMetadataXML(si, metadataFilePath)
Dim MetadataDimensions As List(Of DimInfo) = Me.GetDimensionsInMetadataXML(si, xml)
Dim DimensionStrings As New List(Of String)() For Each di As DimInfo In MetadataDimensions If di.IsNew Then DimensionStrings.Add($"{di.DimTypeObj.Abbrev}#{di.DimName} (new)") Else DimensionStrings.Add($"{di.DimTypeObj.Abbrev}#{di.DimName}") End If Next
BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "pMetadataDimensions_OP_MLE", String.Join(", ", DimensionStrings))
selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True Return selectionChangedTaskResult
#End Region
#Region "Execute Metadata Load"
ElseIf args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ExecuteMetadataLoad") Then
Dim fileLoaded As Boolean = False Dim isValidFile As Boolean = True Dim errorMessage As New StringBuilder
Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
'=== Get options === Dim metadataFilePath As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pImportFileLocation_OP_MLE") Dim storeBackup As Boolean = Convert.ToBoolean(args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pStoreMetadataBackup_OP_MLE")) Dim backupFolder As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pBackupFolder_OP_MLE") Dim replaceMode As Boolean = Convert.ToBoolean(args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pReplaceMode_OP_MLE")) Dim createSecGroups As Boolean = Convert.ToBoolean(args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pCreateMissingSecGroups_OP_MLE")) Dim createPlugs As Boolean = Convert.ToBoolean(args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pCreatePlugAccounts_OP_MLE"))
'=== Get metadata file === Dim xml As String = Me.GetMetadataXML(si, metadataFilePath) Dim fileName As String = Path.GetFileName(metadataFilePath)
'=== Validate file === Dim appXmlFileType As ApplicationXmlFileType = ApplicationXmlFileTypeHelper.GetTypeFromXmlText(xml) Dim sysXmlFileType As SystemXmlFileType = SystemXmlFileTypeHelper.GetTypeFromXmlText(xml) Dim options As New XmlLoadOptions
If appXmlFileType = ApplicationXmlFileType.Metadata And sysXmlFileType = SystemXmlFileType.Unknown Then isValidFile = True Else isValidFile = False errorMessage.AppendLine("Load failed. File must be a valid metadata XML file.") End If
'=== Take backup === If isValidFile And storeBackup Then Me.StoreBackup(si, backupFolder) End If
'=== Clear relationships (replace mode) === If isValidFile And replaceMode Then Dim DimInfos As List(Of DimInfo) = Me.GetDimensionsInMetadataXML(si, xml) Dim DimsToClear As New List(Of [Dim]) Dim CurDim As [Dim]
For Each di As DimInfo In DimInfos If Not di.IsNew Then CurDim = BRApi.Finance.Dim.GetDim(si, di.DimName) DimsToClear.Add(CurDim) End If Next
Me.ClearRelationships(si, DimsToClear) End If
'=== Create missing security groups (entity load) === If isValidFile And createSecGroups Then Me.CreateMissingEntitySecurityGroups(si, xml) End If
'=== Create missing plug accounts (account load) === If isValidFile And createPlugs Then Me.CreateMissingPlugAccounts(si, xml) End If
'=== Load metadata === If isValidFile = True Then Dim task As TaskActivityItem = XmlLoadWcf.StartLoadXml(si, xml, Nothing, fileName, sysXmlFileType, appXmlFileType, options) fileLoaded = True End If
'Delete the temp file BRApi.FileSystem.DeleteFile(si, FileSystemLocation.ApplicationDatabase, metadataFilePath) BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "pMetadataDimensions_OP_MLE", "")
If fileLoaded = True Then selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = $"Metadata load started. Check progress in task activity." Else selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = errorMessage.ToString() End If
Return selectionChangedTaskResult
#End Region
#Region "Execute Entity Security Group Nesting"
ElseIf args.FunctionName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("ExecuteEntitySecurityGroupNesting") Then
Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
'=== Get options === Dim propertiesList As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pSecurityNestingProperties_OP_MLE") 'From bound list property as comma separated list -> convert propertiesList = String.Join(";", propertiesList.Split(",")) 'From text box -> should be semicolon separated already Dim topEntityForNesting As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pTopEntityForNesting_OP_MLE") Dim prefixesList As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pSecurityNestingPrefixes_OP_MLE") Dim replaceModeNesting As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pReplaceModeNesting_OP_MLE") Dim addReadToReadWrite As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("pAddReadToReadWrite_OP_MLE")
Dim customSubstVars As New Dictionary(Of String, String) From { {"bDebug", "False"}, {"lProperties", propertiesList}, {"topEntityForNesting", topEntityForNesting}, {"lPrefixes", prefixesList}, {"bReplaceModeNesting", replaceModeNesting}, {"bAddReadToReadWrite", addReadToReadWrite} }
'Handle incorrect inputs If prefixesList = "" Then selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = $"Entity security group prefixes are missing. Prefixes are mandatory. Nesting not started."
Return selectionChangedTaskResult End If
Dim objTaskActivityItem As TaskActivityItem = BRApi.Utilities.StartDataMgmtSequence(si, "EntitySecurityGroupNesting", customSubstVars)
selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = $"Nesting started. Check progress in task activity."
Return selectionChangedTaskResult
#End Region
#End Region
Else 'This code sets up a TaskResult value Dim taskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult taskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True taskResult.Message = "Unknown Function encounterd" Return taskResult End If End Select
Return Nothing Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
#Region "Settings Helpers"
Private Shared Function DropSolutionTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As String Try 'Open the DDL script used to create the custom tables required for this solution Dim message As String = ""
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then 'Get the SQL from the TableDrop file in the dashboard Dim setupFileName As String = "TableDrop_OP_MLET.txt" Dim fileResource As DashboardFileResource = BRApi.Dashboards.FileResources.GetFileResource(si, False, Guid.Empty, setupFileName) If fileResource Is Nothing Then message = "Table Drop File (" & setupFileName & ") is missing or invalid." Else 'Define string to hold SQL table drop script Dim sqlScript As String = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(fileResource.FileBytes)
'Create connection to application database Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Try 'Create the dashboard Table(s) from the defined script BRApi.Database.ExecuteActionQuery(dbConnApp, sqlScript, False, True)
'Message that tables dropped successfully message = "Solution Tables and Data Uninstalled"
Catch tableEX As Exception 'Message that table drop failed message = "Error: Solution Tables and Data NOT Uninstalled" End Try End Using
End If Else message = "Security Error: Adminstration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall" End If
Return message
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in DropSolutionTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function UninstallSolution(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Uninstall UI, BRs and Drop Solution Tables Dim solutionCode As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_MLEH") Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult() Dim message As New Text.StringBuilder
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then 'Uninstall the Solution Dim uninstallType As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("Type", "UI")
'Evaluate the uninstall type If uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Full") Then 'Drop all associated database tables
'=== Change to OP template - OP_MLE does not create any tables === Dim dropMessage As String = "No database tables dropped; none were created during install" 'Dim dropMessage As String = DropSolutionTables(si) message.AppendLine(dropMessage) End If
If uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("UI") Or uninstallType.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Full") Then 'Remove the UI (Maintenance Unit & BRs) Try 'Delete Solution Dashboard Maintenance Unit, all child items of that Dashboard Maintenance Unit and the Dashboard Profile ' BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.DeleteMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.MaintUnitID, True) Me.DeleteDMUAndProfile(si, args)
'Delete Solution BR's Me.DropSolutionBRs(si)
'Delete Solution Data Management Groups Me.DropSolutionDM(si, "Metadata Load Enhanced (OP_MLE)")
message.AppendLine("User Interface Uninstalled") message.AppendLine("To Complete the Process:") message.AppendLine("1) Close the Dialog") message.AppendLine("2) Close the Dashboard Page")
Catch tableEX As Exception If message.Length = 0 Then message.Append("Error: User Interface & Business Rules NOT Fully Uninstalled.") Else message.AppendLine("Error: User Interface & Business Rules NOT Fully Uninstalled.") End If End Try End If
'Log the Uninstall BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, $"Solution ({solutionCode}) was uninstalled [Type: {uninstallType}]{Environment.NewLine}")
Else message.Append("Security Error: Adminstration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall.") End If
'Set the return value selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = message.ToString
Return selectionChangedTaskResult
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Function
Private Function DropSolutionBRs(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As String Try 'Delete business rules associated with this app Dim message As String = String.Empty Dim dsbBusinessRules As New Dictionary(Of String, BusinessRuleType) From { {"OP_MLE_SolutionHelper", BusinessRuleType.DashboardExtender}, {"OP_MLE_ParamHelper", BusinessRuleType.DashboardStringFunction}, {"OP_MLE_HelperQueries", BusinessRuleType.DashboardDataSet}, {"OP_MLE_DataMgmt", BusinessRuleType.Extender} }
If BRApi.Security.Authorization.IsUserInAdminGroup(si) Then Dim frameworkObject As New Framework
'Get/Delete Dashboard Business Rules For Each br As KeyValuePair(Of String, BusinessRuleType) In dsbBusinessRules Dim brInfo As BusinessRuleInfo = frameworkObject.GetBusinessRule(si, False, br.Value, br.Key) If brInfo IsNot Nothing Then frameworkObject.DeleteBusinessRule(si, False, br.Value, br.Key) End If Next Else message = "Security Error: Administration Rights Required to Execute Uninstall." End If
Return message
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try
End Function
Private Sub DeleteDMUAndProfile(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) Try 'Delete the dashboard profile associated with this solution Dim maintUnit As DashboardMaintUnit = Nothing 'Get the Dashboard Maintenance Unit to delete " + Chr(34) + "XFCS Solution Name (OP_MLE)" + Chr(34) + " maintUnit = BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.GetMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.WorkspaceID, "Metadata Load Enhanced (OP_MLE)") If maintUnit IsNot Nothing Then 'Delete Solution Maintenance and all child items BRApi.Dashboards.MaintUnits.DeleteMaintUnit(si, False, args.PrimaryDashboard.MaintUnitID, True) End If
'Delete Solution Dashboard Profile Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Using dbConnFW As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) Dim dashProfile As DashboardProfile = Nothing dashProfile = EngineDashboardProfiles.GetProfile(dbConnApp, "Metadata Load Enhanced (OP_MLE)") If dashProfile IsNot Nothing Then SecurityHelperWcf.ValidateDelete(dbConnFW, dbConnApp, DashboardHelperWcf.GetRoleType(True), dashProfile, throwOnError:=True) EngineDashboardProfiles.DeleteProfile(dbConnApp, dashProfile.UniqueID) End If End Using End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, ex)) End Try End Sub
Private Sub DropSolutionDM(ByVal si As SessionInfo, Optional groupName As String = "") Try 'Delete data management associated with this app Using dbConnFramework As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si)
Dim dmGroupId As Guid = Guid.Empty 'Get UniqueID for the DataMgmtGroup to be removed Dim dmGroups As List(Of DataMgmtGroup) = DataMgmtProfilesWcf.GetAllGroups(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp) If Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(groupName) Then For Each Group As DataMgmtGroup In dmGroups If Group.Name = groupName Then dmGroupId = Group.UniqueID End If Next End If
If Not dmGroupId = Guid.Empty Then 'Delete DataMgmtSequence Dim sequences As List(Of DataMgmtSequence) = DataMgmtSequencesWcf.GetSequencesInGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) For Each dmSequence As DataMgmtSequence In sequences DataMgmtSequencesWcf.DeleteSequence(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmSequence.UniqueID) Next
'Delete DataMgmtSeqStepMember Dim steps As List(Of DataMgmtStepSummaryInfo) = DataMgmtStepsWcf.GetStepsInGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) For Each dmStep As DataMgmtStepSummaryInfo In steps DataMgmtStepsWcf.DeleteStep(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmStep.UniqueID) Next
' Delete the DataMgmtGroup DataMgmtProfilesWcf.DeleteGroup(dbConnFramework, dbConnApp, dmGroupId) End If
End Using End Using Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in DropSolutionDM() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function CreateStandardTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) If Not DbSql.DoesTableExist(dbConnApp, "XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists") Then Dim SetupFileName As String = "TableSetup_OP_MLET.txt" Dim fileResource As DashboardFileResource = BRApi.Dashboards.FileResources.GetFileResource(si, False, Guid.Empty, SetupFileName) If fileResource Is Nothing Then selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = $"Table Setup File ({SetupFileName}) is missing or invalid." Return selectionChangedTaskResult End If
Try Dim sqlScript As String = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(fileResource.FileBytes) BRApi.Database.ExecuteActionQuery(dbConnApp, sqlScript, False, True) selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Setup Completed"
Catch TableEX As Exception 'Message that tables creation failed selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Error: Solution Tables NOT Created" End Try Else 'Nothing to do selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Setup Completed" End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult End Using Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in CreateStandardTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function GetCurrentVersionDataTable(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As DataTable Try Dim OP_MLE_CurrentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) 'Define the SQL Statement Dim sql As String = $"Select * From XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists Where ListName = '{OP_MLE_CurrentVersion}'"
'Return the DataTable 'Create Standard Resource Tables Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) If (DbSql.DoesTableExist(dbConnApp, "XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists")) Then Return BRApi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConnApp, sql, False) End If End Using Return Nothing
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function GetCurrentSolutionVersion(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As Integer Try Dim currentVersion As Integer = SharedConstants.Unknown 'Return the DataTable Using dt As DataTable = GetCurrentVersionDataTable(si) If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count = 1 Then currentVersion = ConvertHelper.ToInt32(dt(0)("StoredValue")) End If End If End Using Return currentVersion Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Public Function GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(ByVal si As SessionInfo) As Integer Try Dim version As Integer = SharedConstants.Unknown Dim dbParamVersion As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutVersion_OP_MLEH") Dim pv As String = String.Empty Dim sv As String = String.Empty
'Param Version should be in XXX PV440 SV100 format. If Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(dbParamVersion) Then Dim mc As RegularExpressions.MatchCollection = Regex.Matches(dbParamVersion, "^.*PV(\d+)-SV(\d+)") If mc.Count > 0 Then Dim m As System.Text.RegularExpressions.Match = mc(0) pv = m.Groups(1).Value sv = m.Groups(2).Value Else Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If Else Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If
'Each Version Should be 3 Characters. Validate/Error if this isn't True. If (Not pv.Length = 3) Or (Not sv.Length = 3) Then Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, "Error: Solution Version Invalid") End If
version = ConvertHelper.ToInt32(pv & sv)
Return version
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Function CreateSolutionTables(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Create or Upgrade the solution schema Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult()
'=== Change to OP template - OP_MLE does not create any tables === selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "No setup needed - MLE does not create any new database tables" Return selectionChangedTaskResult
'Validate Setup is not a downgrade Dim prevVersion As Integer = GetCurrentSolutionVersion(si) Dim currentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) If (prevVersion > currentVersion) And (prevVersion <> SharedConstants.Unknown) Then Dim solutionCode As String = BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.GetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "HelpAboutSolutionCode_OP_MLEH") Throw New XFUserMsgException(si, Nothing, Nothing, StringHelper.FormatMessage("Critical Error: Setup Aborted. Unable to downgrade from {0} {1} to {0} {2} without first executing a full uninstall or {0} {1}.", solutionCode, prevVersion, currentVersion)) End If
'Create Standard Tables to hold version info and settings selectionChangedTaskResult = CreateStandardTables(si)
'New Install (Create Tables and Return) 'If IsOk Is returned Then, the table was created As a New install - Return the result If selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK Then ' Update the default dashboard UpdateDefaultDashBoard(si, args, selectionChangedTaskResult) 'Update Stored Current Version StoreCurrentSolutionVersion(si, currentVersion) 'Attempt to Reset the Old Global Settings if they exist RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions(si)
Return selectionChangedTaskResult End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in CreateSolutionTables() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Shared Sub UpdateDefaultDashBoard(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByRef args As DashboardExtenderArgs, ByRef selectionChangedTaskResult As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult) Try 'Get values for passed parameter Dim defaultPage As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("DefaultPage", SharedConstants.Unknown.ToString) 'Set dashboardDB to Open BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, "MainDashboardName_OP_MLES", defaultPage) selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars("MainDashboardName_OP_MLES") = defaultPage selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars = args.SelectionChangedTaskInfo.CustomSubstVars Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in UpdateDefaultDashBoard() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable(ByVal si As SessionInfo, Optional ByVal storedSettingsTableGroup As String = "") As DataTable Try Dim XFW_LastSavedSettings As String = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) 'Define the SQL Statement Dim sql As String = String.Empty If storedSettingsTableGroup = "All" Then sql = $"SELECT * FROM XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists WHERE ListName = 'XFW_OP_MLE_GlobalSettings' OR ListName = 'XFW_OP_MLE_LCRSettings' OR ListName = 'XFW_OP_MLE_MFBSettings' AND StoredValue = '{XFW_LastSavedSettings}'" Else sql = $"SELECT * From XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists WHERE ListName = '{storedSettingsTableGroup}' AND StoredValue = '{XFW_LastSavedSettings}'" End If
'Return the DataTable Using dbConnApp As DbConnInfo = BRApi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si) Return BRApi.Database.ExecuteSql(dbConnApp, sql, False) End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
Private Sub RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions(ByVal si As SessionInfo) Try 'Get the last stored settings value string in the Control tables and update the Literal Parameters Using dt As DataTable = Me.GetSettingsStorageForUpgradeDataTable(si, "All") If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count > 0 Then 'Get the last stored settings values and update the global options For Each settingsRow As DataRow In dt.Rows Dim dr As DataRow = settingsRow Dim nvb As New NameValueFormatBuilder(CType(dr("DisplayValue"), String)) 'Loop over the name value pairs and update the corresponding literal parameters If nvb IsNot Nothing Then For Each kvp As KeyValuePair(Of String, String) In nvb.NameValuePairs BRApi.Dashboards.Parameters.SetLiteralParameterValue(si, False, kvp.Key, kvp.Value) Next End If Next End If End If End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in RestoreLastSaveGlobalOptions() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Sub StoreCurrentSolutionVersion(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal version As Integer) Try Using dt As DataTable = Me.GetCurrentVersionDataTable(si) Dim OP_MLE_CurrentVersion As Integer = GetCurrentVersionFromDashboardParam(si) If dt IsNot Nothing Then If dt.Rows.Count = 0 Then 'NEW: Store the last setup version Dim dr As DataRow = dt.NewRow dr("ListName") = OP_MLE_CurrentVersion dr("StoredValue") = version.ToString dr("DisplayValue") = version.ToString dr("Description") = si.UserName dr("Active") = False dt.Rows.Add(dr) Else 'Update: Store the last setup version Dim dr As DataRow = dt.Rows(0) dr.BeginEdit() dr("ListName") = OP_MLE_CurrentVersion dr("StoredValue") = version.ToString dr("DisplayValue") = version.ToString dr("Description") = si.UserName dr("Active") = False dr.EndEdit() End If
'Execute the save BRApi.Database.SaveCustomDataTable(si, "App", "XFW_OP_MLE_ControlLists", dt, False) End If End Using
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in StoreCurrentSolusionVersion() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Public Sub AddOrUpdateDictionary(ByRef modifiedVars As Dictionary(Of String, String), key As String, value As String) If (modifiedVars.ContainsKey(key)) Then modifiedVars(key) = value Else modifiedVars.Add(key, value) End If End Sub
Private Sub SetDashboards(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal solutionCode As String, ByRef modifiedVars As Dictionary(Of String, String), Optional ByVal parameterName As String = Nothing, Optional ByVal dashboardName As String = Nothing) Try
AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, "Toolbar_OP_MLE", "2_Toolbar_OP_MLE" & solutionCode) AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, "SelectedContentDashboard_OP_MLE", "3_Content_OP_MLE" & solutionCode)
If (Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(dashboardName) AndAlso Not String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(parameterName)) Then AddOrUpdateDictionary(modifiedVars, parameterName, dashboardName) End If Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in SetDashboards() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Sub
Private Function ValidateSetupStepsExecuted(ByVal si As SessionInfo, ByVal args As DashboardExtenderArgs) As XFSelectionChangedTaskResult Try 'Validate that the user has executed the setup steps '---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Dim selectionChangedTaskResult As New XFSelectionChangedTaskResult() Dim mainDashboardName As String = args.NameValuePairs.XFGetValue("MainDashboardName", SharedConstants.Unknown.ToString) Dim modifiedVars As New Dictionary(Of String, String)
'If the user executed the setup steps, the MainDashboardName will no longer equal the name of the setup dashboard Dim setupDashboardName As String = "0_Frame_OP_MLET" If mainDashboardName.XFEqualsIgnoreCase(setupDashboardName) Then 'User has NOT executed the setup steps selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = False selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = True selectionChangedTaskResult.Message = "Please execute all required setup steps prior to launching the solution" selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeSelectionChangedNavigationInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationType = XFSelectionChangedNavigationType.NoAction selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationArgs = "" Else 'Launch the page selectionChangedTaskResult.IsOK = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ShowMessageBox = False SetDashboards(si, "", modifiedVars, "SelectedContent_OP_MLE", "3_Content_OP_MLEM") selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeCustomSubstVarsInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedCustomSubstVars = modifiedVars selectionChangedTaskResult.ChangeSelectionChangedNavigationInDashboard = True selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationType = XFSelectionChangedNavigationType.OpenPage selectionChangedTaskResult.ModifiedSelectionChangedNavigationInfo.SelectionChangedNavigationArgs = "XFPage=Dashboard:0_Frame_OP_MLE_OnePlace" End If Return selectionChangedTaskResult
Catch ex As Exception Throw ErrorHandler.LogWrite(si, New XFException(si, "Unhandled Exception in ValidateSetupStepsExecuted() function.", ex.Message, ex.InnerException)) End Try End Function
#End Region
#Region "Error Messages"
#End Region
#Region "OP_MLE Custom Helpers"
#Region "Get metadata XML"
Private Function GetMetadataXML(si As SessionInfo, filePath As String) As String
Dim fileInfo As XFFileEx = BRApi.FileSystem.GetFile(si, FileSystemLocation.ApplicationDatabase, filePath, True, True) Dim xml As String = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(fileinfo.XFFile.ContentFileBytes)
'Trim BOM if exists xml = xml.TrimStart(ChrW(&HFEFF))
Return xml End Function
#End Region
#Region "Store backup"
Private Sub StoreBackup(si As SessionInfo, backupFolder As String)
Using dbConnFW As DBConnInfo = BRAPi.Database.CreateFrameworkDbConnInfo(si) Using dbConnApp As DBConnInfo = BRAPi.Database.CreateApplicationDbConnInfo(si)
Dim backupFileName As String = $"OP_MLE_Metadata_Backup_{DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss")}.xml"
Dim ExtractDimOptions As New XmlExtractMetadataDimOptions(True, True, False, Nothing, Nothing, Nothing, Nothing) Dim dimOptionsByDimPk As New Dictionary(Of DimPk, XmlExtractMetadataDimOptions) Dim xmlExtractTypes As New Dictionary(Of XmlExtractItemPk, Boolean) xmlExtractTypes.Add(New XmlExtractItemPk(XmlExtractItemType.Dimensions), True)
Dim Dims As List(Of [Dim]) = GetNonHardCodedDims(si) For Each D As [Dim] In Dims dimOptionsByDimPk.Add(D.DimPk, ExtractDimOptions) xmlExtractTypes.Add(New XmlExtractItemPk(XmlExtractItemType.Dimension, D.DimPk.DimId), True) Next
Dim xmlMetadataOptions As New XmlExtractMetadataOptions(dimOptionsByDimPk) Dim xmlOptions As New XmlExtractOptions(False, False, Nothing, Nothing, xmlMetadataOptions)
Dim xmlExtract As String = MetadataExtract.ExtractXml(dbConnFW, dbConnApp, xmlOptions, xmlExtractTypes) Dim fileBytes As Byte() = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(xmlExtract)
Dim dbFileInfo As New XFFileInfo(FileSystemLocation.ApplicationDatabase, backupFileName, backupFolder, XFFileType.Unknown) dbFileInfo.ContentFileContainsData = True dbFileInfo.ContentFileExtension = dbFileInfo.Extension Dim dbFile As New XFFile(dbFileInfo, String.Empty, fileBytes) BRApi.FileSystem.InsertOrUpdateFile(si, dbFile)
End Using End Using
End Sub
#End Region
#Region "Clear Relationships"
Private Sub ClearRelationships(si As SessionInfo, Dims As List(Of [Dim]))
For Each D In Dims If D.IsRootDim Then Continue For End If
Dim Members As List(Of Member) = BRApi.Finance.Members.GetAllMembers(si, D.DimPk, False) Dim RelationshipsToDelete As List(Of RelationshipPk) = New List(Of RelationshipPk) For Each M In Members Dim Relationships As List(Of Relationship) = BRApi.Finance.Members.ReadParentRelationshipsNoCache(si, M.DimTypeId, M.MemberId) For Each R In Relationships RelationshipsToDelete.Add(R.RelationshipPk) Next Next
BRApi.Finance.MemberAdmin.RemoveRelationships(si, D.DimPk, RelationshipsToDelete, True) Next
End Sub
#End Region
#Region "Create missing security groups (entity load)"
Private Sub CreateMissingEntitySecurityGroups(si As SessionInfo, xml As String) Dim XmlDoc As XDocument = XDocument.Parse(xml)
Dim Members As IEnumerable(Of XElement) = XmlDoc _ .Descendants("dimension") _ .Where(Function(x) x.Attribute("type").Value.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Entity")) _ .Descendants("member")
'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, "Members: " + String.Join(",", Members.Select(Function(m) m.Name)))
'Read entity group assignments from XML Dim GroupNames As List(Of String) = New List(Of String) For Each el As XElement In Members GroupNames.Add(el.Attribute("displayMemberGroup").Value) GroupNames.Add(el.Attribute("readDataGroup").Value) GroupNames.Add(el.Attribute("readDataGroup2").Value) GroupNames.Add(el.Attribute("readWriteDataGroup").Value) GroupNames.Add(el.Attribute("readWriteDataGroup2").Value) Next GroupNames = GroupNames.Distinct().ToList()
'Create missing security groups For Each GroupName In GroupNames Dim GroupInfo As GroupInfo = BRApi.Security.Admin.GetGroup(si, GroupName)
If GroupInfo IsNot Nothing Then 'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, "Found: " + GroupInfo.Group.Name) Else Dim NewGroupInfo As GroupInfo = New GroupInfo() Dim NewGroup As New OneStream.Shared.Wcf.Group With {.Name = GroupName} NewGroupInfo.Group = NewGroup
BRApi.Security.Admin.SaveGroup(si, NewGroupInfo, False, Nothing, TriStateBool.Unknown) 'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, "Created new group: " + NewGroupInfo.Group.Name) End If Next End Sub
#End Region
#Region "Create missing plug accounts (account load)"
Private Sub CreateMissingPlugAccounts(si As SessionInfo, xml As String) Dim XmlDoc As XDocument = XDocument.Parse(xml)
'Account name and dimension needed to create plug 'Dimension is four levels up from property in metadata XML Dim PlugPropertyAndDimension As IEnumerable(Of Object) = _ From el In XmlDoc _ .Descendants("dimension") _ .Where(Function(x) x.Attribute("type").Value.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("Account")) _ .Descendants("member") _ .Descendants("property") _ .Where(Function(el) el.Attribute("name").Value.XFEqualsIgnoreCase("PlugAccount") And el.Attribute("value").Value <> "") _ .Select(Function(el) { el.Attribute("value").Value, _ el.Parent.Parent.Parent.Parent.Attribute("name").Value.ToString() })
'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, "PlugPropertyAndDimension: " + String.Join(",", PlugPropertyAndDimension.Select(Function(arr) $"{arr(0)}|{arr(1)}")))
For Each Pair In PlugPropertyAndDimension Dim PlugAccountName As String = Pair(0) Dim DimName As String = Pair(1)
Dim PlugAccount As Member = BRApi.Finance.Members.GetMember(si, DimType.Account.Id, PlugAccountName) If PlugAccount Is Nothing Then Dim Dimension As [Dim] = BRApi.Finance.Dim.GetDim(si, DimName) Dim NewPlug As New Member(memberPk.CreateAll(DimType.Account.Id), PlugAccountName, "", Dimension.DimPk.DimId)
'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, "Saving new plug account: PlugAccountName")
BRApi.Finance.MemberAdmin.SaveMemberInfo(si, True, NewPlug, False, Nothing, False, Nothing, True) End If Next End Sub
#End Region
#Region "Get dimensions from XML file"
Structure DimInfo Public DimTypeObj As DimType Public DimName As String Public IsNew As Boolean End Structure
Private Function GetDimensionsInMetadataXML(si As SessionInfo, xml As String) As List(Of DimInfo) Dim XmlDoc As XDocument = XDocument.Parse(xml)
Dim Dims As New List(Of DimInfo) For Each el In XmlDoc.Root.Descendants("dimension") Dim di As DimInfo
di.DimName = el.Attribute("name").Value di.DimTypeObj = DimType.GetItem(el.Attribute("type").Value)
Dim DimObj As [Dim] = BRApi.Finance.Dim.GetDim(si, di.DimName)
If DimObj Is Nothing Then di.IsNew = True Else di.IsNew = False End If
Dims.Add(di) Next
Return Dims End Function
#End Region
#Region "Dim helpers"
Public Function GetNonHardCodedDims(si As SessionInfo) As List(Of [Dim])
Dim DimTypes As List(Of DimType) = DimType.GetAllDimTypes() Dim Dims As New List(Of [Dim])()
For Each CurrentDimType In DimTypes For Each CurrentDim In BRApi.Finance.Dim.GetDims(si, CurrentDimType.Id) If CurrentDim.IsRootDim Then 'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, $"Root Dim {CurrentDim.Name} skipped") Continue For Else If CurrentDim.IsHardCodedDimType Then 'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, $"Hard coded Dim {CurrentDim.Name} skipped") Continue For End If
Dims.Add(CurrentDim) 'BRApi.ErrorLog.LogMessage(si, $"{CurrentDimType.Id}:{CurrentDimType.Name} - {CurrentDim.DimPk.DimId}:{CurrentDim.Name} added to Dims") Next Next
Return Dims
End Function
Public Function GetAllMembersInDims(si As SessionInfo, Dims As List(Of [Dim])) As List(Of Member)
Dim Members As New List(Of [Member])()
For Each CurrentDim In Dims For Each CurrentMember In BRApi.Finance.Members.GetAllMembers(si, CurrentDim.DimPk, False) If Not CurrentMember.IsNone Then Members.Add(CurrentMember) End If Next Next
Return Members
End Function
Public Function GetAllMembers(si As SessionInfo) As List(Of Member)
Dim Dims As List(Of [Dim]) = GetNonHardCodedDims(si) Dim Members As List(Of Member) = GetAllMembersInDims(si, Dims)
Return Members
End Function
#End Region
#End Region
End Class End Namespace

component.name: txt_SecurityNestingPrefixes_OP_MLE
component.toolTip: Semicolon separated list of prefixes used to identify entity security groups (e.g. E_R_ and E_RW_). Only groups with these prefixes will be added/removed during nesting. Mandatory for security reasons. If you have, for example, assigned Administrators group to some entity manually, you probably never want this to be automatically nested to parent groups. You may also have manually assigned non-entity groups within entity groups that you don't wish to be unnested when using replace mode. Prefixes ensure this doesn't happen accidentally.
component.displayFormat: HorizontalAlignment = Left, LabelBold = True, LabelPosition = Top, MarginLeft = 10, MarginTop = 10, Width = 300

component.name: txt_TopEntityForNesting_OP_MLE
component.toolTip: If you want to only apply nesting to a particular (sub-)hierarchy, enter the name of the parent entity here. To nest security groups for all hierarchies, leave the box empty.
